omposed of numbers\nand/or percentages. The string value `'default'` can also be passed to\nexplicitly select the terminal default colour.\n\nNote: alpha values are accepted, but ignored and discarded.\n\n```\nparam value\n\n\n\nparam background\n\n\n\nparam web_palette_only\n\nif true, use the web palette for all named\ncolours instead of falling back to terminal palette for basic\nCGA colours\n\nreturn\n\nSGR\n```\n"]}, {"name": "pansi.text.color", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "web_palette_only", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generate ANSI escape code string for given foreground colour value.\n    "]}, {"name": "pansi.text.background_color", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "web_palette_only", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generate ANSI escape code string for given background colour value.\n    "]}, {"name": "pansi.text.font_weight", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generate ANSI escape sequence for the given font weight. Values\ncorrespond to CSS font-weight values 'bold' and 'normal' or numeric\nequivalents.\n\n```pycon\n>>> font_weight('bold')\n'\\x1b[1m'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "pansi.text.font_style", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generate ANSI escape sequence for the given font style.\n    "]}, {"name": "pansi.text.text_decoration", "asynchronous": 